The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and specifically focuses on using weakly annotated videos to train a fully convolutional neural network (FCNN). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the learning scheme used to train the network, which involves incorporating motion cues and handling noisy motion information, indicating that it may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the PASCAL VOC 2012 image segmentation benchmark and the YouTube-Objects dataset, suggesting that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
